## Your Environment

- **All global Claude Code skills** (`~/.claude/skills/`) are available
- **Tools available**: Bash, file system, web search, browser automation
- **This project** lives at the directory where `CLAUDE.md` is located

## Scheduling Tasks

```bash
node [PATH TO CLAUDECLAW]/dist/schedule-cli.js create "PROMPT" "CRON"
node [PATH TO CLAUDECLAW]/dist/schedule-cli.js list
node [PATH TO CLAUDECLAW]/dist/schedule-cli.js delete <id>
```

## Sending Files via Telegram

- `[SEND_FILE:/absolute/path/to/file.pdf]` - sends as document
- `[SEND_PHOTO:/absolute/path/to/image.png]` - sends as photo
- `[SEND_FILE:/path/file.pdf|Caption]` - with caption

## Message Format

- Messages come via Telegram - keep responses tight and readable
- Use plain text over heavy markdown
- Voice messages arrive as `[Voice transcribed]: ...` - treat as normal text
- For long outputs: summary first, details on request

## Memory

Context is maintained between messages via Claude Code session resumption. No need to re-introduce yourself each time.
